parameters: ...It feels disgusting. It's like being inside the rotten guts of a fish.

(...His presence is elusive... It's like watching him through a paper
screen...)

(...Even if I'm lost, it's no good. I have to find him, protect him, and
then... ...guide him to escape.)
(...I wonder if he will obediently follow my guidance...)

(I wonder if he realizes? Even though Araka is doing so much for him!
Being oblivious is a sin, isn't it, Araka?)

Explanation of the Araka Part System: In the Araka Part, events occur
where Araka is strengthened or weakened depending on the choices you
make in the Horror Part.

When investigating the ominous things persistently in the Horror Part,
Araka will try to help you and end up suffering in a pitiful way,
resulting in weakening and experiencing aftereffects.

When taking actions that benefit Araka in the Horror
Part, Araka may be strengthened.

In this game, even if you lose, the story will continue. Additionally,
there are rescue measures that allow you to reach the true end even if
you make wrong choices in the Horror Part.
